SKILL|excalidraw|"Hand-drawn Excalidraw JSON diagrams (arch, flow, seq)."
STEP|1|**Load this skill** (you already did)
STEP|2|**Write the elements JSON** -- an array of Excalidraw element objects
STEP|3|**Save the file** using `write_file` to create a `.excalidraw` file
STEP|4|**Optionally upload** for a shareable link using `scripts/upload.py` via `terminal`
STEP|5|`strokeColor`: `"#1e1e1e"`
STEP|6|`backgroundColor`: `"transparent"`
STEP|7|`fillStyle`: `"solid"`
STEP|8|`strokeWidth`: `2`
STEP|9|`roughness`: `1` (hand-drawn look)
STEP|10|`opacity`: `100`
STEP|11|Rectangle**:
STEP|12|`roundness: { "type": 3 }` for rounded corners
STEP|13|`backgroundColor: "#a5d8ff"`, `fillStyle: "solid"` for filled
STEP|14|Ellipse**:
STEP|15|Diamond**:
STEP|16|Labeled shape (container binding)** -- create a text element bound to the shape:
STEP|17|Works on rectangle, ellipse, diamond
STEP|18|Text is auto-centered by Excalidraw when `containerId` is set
STEP|19|The text `x`/`y`/`width`/`height` are approximate -- Excalidraw recalculates them on load
STEP|20|`originalText` should match `text`
STEP|21|Always include `fontFamily: 1` (Virgil/hand-drawn font)
STEP|22|Labeled arrow** -- same container binding approach:
STEP|23|Standalone text** (titles and annotations only -- no container):
STEP|24|`x` is the LEFT edge. To center at position `cx`: `x = cx - (text.length * fontSize * 0.5) / 2`
STEP|25|Do NOT rely on `textAlign` or `width` for positioning
STEP|26|Arrow**:
STEP|27|`points`: `[dx, dy]` offsets from element `x`, `y`
STEP|28|`endArrowhead`: `null` \| `"arrow"` \| `"bar"` \| `"dot"` \| `"triangle"`
STEP|29|`strokeStyle`: `"solid"` (default) \| `"dashed"` \| `"dotted"`
STEP|30|Array order = z-order (first = back, last = front)
STEP|31|Emit progressively: background zones → shape → its bound text → its arrows → next shape
STEP|32|BAD: all rectangles, then all texts, then all arrows
STEP|33|GOOD: bg_zone → shape1 → text_for_shape1 → arrow1 → arrow_label_text → shape2 → text_for_shape2 → ...
STEP|34|Always place the bound text element immediately after its container shape
STEP|35|Font sizes:**
STEP|36|Minimum `fontSize`: **16** for body text, labels, descriptions
STEP|37|Minimum `fontSize`: **20** for titles and headings
STEP|38|Minimum `fontSize`: **14** for secondary annotations only (sparingly)
STEP|39|NEVER use `fontSize` below 14
STEP|40|Element sizes:**
STEP|41|Minimum shape size: 120x60 for labeled rectangles/ellipses
STEP|42|Leave 20-30px gaps between elements minimum
STEP|43|Prefer fewer, larger elements over many tiny ones
STEP|44|Use the color palette consistently across the diagram
STEP|45|**Text contrast is CRITICAL** -- never use light gray on white backgrounds. Minimum text color on white: `#757575`
STEP|46|Do NOT use emoji in text -- they don't render in Excalidraw's font
STEP|47|For dark mode diagrams, see `references/dark-mode.md`
STEP|48|For larger examples, see `references/examples.md`
